#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/marketplace/lean-startup/references/assumptions.md savings=3%
M|Leap|tx|Every startup is built on a stack of unproven assumptions. Most founders treat these assumptions as facts. The Lean Startup treats them as hypotheses that must be tested systematically. Leap-of-faith assumptions are the assumptions that must be true for the business to succeed but have the least evidence supporting them. Identifying, prioritizing, and testing these assumptions is the foundation of validated learning.
M|Valu|The |
M|Valu|tx|Tests whether the pd delivers value to cs once they start using it.
M|Valu|**Co|** Do cs find this pd valuable enough to keep using it (and eventually pay for it)?
M|Valu|tx|\| Dimension \| What to Validate \| Example Signals \|
M|Valu|tx|\|-----------\|-----------------\|-----------------\|
M|Valu|tx|\| Problem existence \| The problem is real and painful enough to motivate action \| cs describe the problem unprompted in interviews \|
M|Valu|tx|\| Solution fit \| Your specific solution addresses the problem effectively \| us complete core tasks successfully; retention is strong \|
M|Valu|tx|\| Willingness to pay \| cs value the solution enough to exchange money for it \| Pre-orders, paid pilots, conversion from free to paid \|
M|Valu|tx|\| Frequency \| cs need the solution repeatedly, not just once \| Return usage within expected timeframe \|
M|Grow|tx|Tests how new cs discover and adopt the pd.
M|Grow|**Co|** How will this pd spread from early adopters to a broader mk?
M|Grow|tx|\| Dimension \| What to Validate \| Example Signals \|
M|Grow|tx|\|-----------\|-----------------\|-----------------\|
M|Grow|tx|\| Discoverability \| Target cs can find the pd \| Organic search traffic, word-of-mouth referrals \|
M|Grow|tx|\| Acquisition cost \| You can acquire cs at a sustainable cost \| CAC below projected LTV \|
M|Grow|tx|\| Virality \| Existing us bring in new us \| Viral coefficient, referral rates, sl sharing \|
M|Grow|tx|\| mk size \| Enough potential cs exist \| TAM al validated by early traction patterns \|
M|Grow|**Cr|** Validate the value hypothesis before the growth hypothesis. Growing something people do not value is the most expensive way to fail.
