M|The |Each|
M|The |tx|1. **State the assumption clearly.** "We assume that ____."
M|The |tx|2. **Identify the riskiest element.** What part of this assumption, if wrong, wld be most damaging?
M|The |tx|3. **Formulate a falsifiable hypothesis.** "If we ____, then ____ will happen within ____."
M|The |tx|4. **Choose the fastest tst method.** What is the minimum effort that generates a meaningful signal?
M|The |tx|5. **Set pass/fail criteria in advance.** "sc = ____. fl = ____."
M|The |tx|6. **Run the experiment.**
M|The |tx|7. **Record the result and decide.** Persevere, pivot, or dig deeper.
M|Exam|**As|** Remote teams need asynchronous vd messaging.
M|Exam|**Ri|** Do remote teams actually feel pain around asynchronous communication, or are Slack and em sufficient?
M|Exam|**Hy|** If we post a landing page describing async vd messaging in 5 remote-work communities, at least 3% of visitors will sign up for the waitlist within 2 weeks.
M|Exam|**Te|** Landing page w/ Mailchimp signup. $200 in targeted ad as supplement to organic posts.
M|Exam|**Pa|** Above 3% signup rate w/ 500+ visitors = proceed. Below 3% = interview signups to understand why, then reassess.
M|Exam|**Re|** 4.2% signup rate. 21 signups. 8 responded to follow-up em. 5 described specific pain points w/ existing tools.
M|Exam|**De|** Assumption partially validated. Proceed to concierge MVP w/ the 8 respondents to validate solution fit.
M|Sequ|Test|
M|Sequ|tx|1. **cs and problem assumptions first.** If the problem does not exist or the cs does not care, nothing else matters.
M|Sequ|tx|2. **Solution assumptions second.** Does your approach actually solve the problem?
M|Sequ|tx|3. **Business md assumptions third.** Can you make money?
M|Sequ|tx|4. **Growth assumptions last.** Can you scale?
M|Sequ|This|building and scaling a solution to a problem nobody has.